{
  "message": "fix: tighten mod tests pattern to avoid false positives\n\nThe previous pattern `^[[:space:]]*mod tests` would incorrectly match\nmodules like `mod tests_helper` or `mod tests_utils`, causing production\ncode in those modules to be excluded when using --exclude-tests.\n\nNow requires `mod tests` to be followed by whitespace, `{`, `;`, or EOL,\npreventing false matches on identifiers that merely start with \"tests\".\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
